; Regression test for issue #562:
; Slow account directives processing.
;
; Account `check` directives are implemented as auto transactions.
; Previously, every posting scanned the entire auto_xacts list to
; find the one(s) applying to its account, giving O(m*n) behavior
; where m is the number of account check directives and n is the
; number of postings.  The fix indexes account-scoped check directives
; by their target account so that extend_xact() dispatches them via
; O(1) lookup.
;
; This test does not measure timing; instead it verifies correctness
; is preserved.  It also exercises paths that would break under a
; naive indexing scheme:
;
;   * multiple `check` expressions on a single account accumulate
;   * checks on different accounts do not cross-trigger
;   * account-scoped checks see postings generated by a regular
;     auto_xact (= /regex/) -- the #1680 invariant must still hold
;   * checks still reach the bucket (default) account when the
;     posting's amount is inferred rather than explicit

commodity $
    format $1,000.00

account Assets:Cash
    check abs(amount) <= 20
    check commodity == '$'
    default

account Assets:Bank
    check commodity == '$'

account Expenses:Food
    check commodity == '$'

account Budget:Food
    check commodity == '$'

; A regular (= /expr/) auto_xact generates postings that the scoped
; checks must be able to see (protects the #1680 invariant).
= /Expenses:Food/
    (Budget:Food)                            -1.0

2012-02-27 KFC
    Expenses:Food                             $10.00
    Assets:Cash

2012-02-28 KFC
    Expenses:Food                             $25.00
    Assets:Bank

; No explicit balancing posting: the bucket account (Assets:Cash,
; marked `default`) fills in, and its check still runs on that
; inferred posting.
2012-02-29 KFC
    Expenses:Food                             $25.00

test reg
12-Feb-27 KFC                   Expenses:Food                $10.00       $10.00
                                Assets:Cash                 $-10.00            0
                                (Budget:Food)               $-10.00      $-10.00
12-Feb-28 KFC                   Expenses:Food                $25.00       $15.00
                                Assets:Bank                 $-25.00      $-10.00
                                (Budget:Food)               $-25.00      $-35.00
12-Feb-29 KFC                   Expenses:Food                $25.00      $-10.00
                                Assets:Cash                 $-25.00      $-35.00
                                (Budget:Food)               $-25.00      $-60.00
__ERROR__
Warning: "$FILE", line 56: Transaction check failed: (abs(amount) <= {20})
  (check expression at "$FILE", line 26)
end test
